<p>I have some problem to update my d3.js table when mousemoving. Here is a simplified <a href="https://jsfiddle.net/lszhou2115/npzjLng9/6/" rel="nofollow">example</a> in jsfiddle.</p>  <p>Here is the main code:</p>  <pre><code> function mousemove() {    var newdata = [{Variable: "x", Value: 1}, {Variable: "y", Value: 1}]    table.selectAll("tbody.tr")     .data(newdata)     .enter()     .append("tr")     .selectAll("td")     .data(function(row) {       return columns.map(function(column) {         return {column: column, value: row[column]};       });     })     .enter()     .append("td")     .text(function(d) { return d.value; }); }; </code></pre>  <p>namely, how can I only update the values in the table instead of drawing a new table again and again?</p>  <p>Thank you!</p>